The paper deals with clustering digital paintings using deep convolutional embedding, which involves computer vision techniques such as feature extraction and dimensionality reduction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as clustering and optimization, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper mentions the use of visual link retrieval and historical knowledge discovery, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a novel deep clustering approach, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
